<TITLE> DU warns 40 latecomers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 03 (bdnews24.com)  Dhaka University warned 40 members of its staff for negligence of their duty on Monday. The administration also issued a show-cause notice on AB Siddiqur Rahman, personal assistant to the vice chancellor. The 40 people, including two assistant registrars Jahangir Morshed and Shehina Akhter, security officer Masud Kamal, were not at work on time on Sunday. The authorities in the evening decided to warn them and announced the matter formally on Monday. Syed Rejaur Rahman, acting registrar of the university, said that there had been no system of attendance monitoring in many sections. "And even if there is, the officer supposed to monitor attendance, is not aware of the responsibility." He said that the authorities would take tough action against the late comers in future. The VC's personal assistant of was asked to explain within 24 hours why he was absent without permission on Sunday. He is accused of not informing the acting VC about the prescheduled meeting of all the VCs at the prime minister's office on Sunday. Siddiqur replied to the notice admitting his fault on Monday. Professor Harun-or-Rashid, acting VC of the university, told journalists that a sudden inspection was made at the administrative building in response to the complaints. He said that the process will continue. bdnews2
